 Vernon is no stranger to being a world record title owner after he set the first Guinness World Record in 1997, by living in a wine barrel at the end of a pole, for 67 days. Many years later, Vernon returned to Dullstroom and attempted to break his own record, after being airlifted into a 500 liter wine barrel, stuck to the end of a 23 meter pole.  Vernon broke his record on Monday 20 January after completing 67 days in his barrel but pushed for more time by staying for five more days. The village of Dullstroom celebrated Vernonâ€™s new record on 25 January (today), after an exhausted Vernon announced that he was coming down. Read more by visiting the following link: Vernon battles the barrel for child welfare